radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is distended, measuring up to 1 cm in diameter with wall hyperenhancement and mild adjacent stranding. No evidence of perforation or abscess formation. No ascites. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. There is no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and distal ureters are unremarkable.
